snippet.textDisplay:
Dear All, please don't spread hate and racism here.. by doing this you are just lowering yourself.., as the saying goes, music and art have no language, religion or barrier. 
These young talented people trying to spread love and care by mixing various languages and melodious instruments. Music is food for soul (mosiqi rooh ki ghaza ha). 
A part of the song (man omade am Ishq faryad ... I have come here on call of Love) is a tribute to madam Gogoosh of Iran, the original song is about 40 years old, but still very popular among farsi speaking nations. 
The rest of the song is in Urdu, which is sung by Mr. Atef Aslam an extremely popular singer in Indian subcontinental. 
Please enjoy the music, the words, the passion and wonderful melodies & tones. Trust me you will feel much better.
God Bless you all.   peace!!
